The Ruy Lopez (Bb5):

Also known as the Spanish Opening, it starts after
1.e4 e5
2.Nf3 Nc6
3.Bb5.

It aims to exert pressure on the e5 pawn and the knight on c6.

This opening is known for its deep strategic complexity.

There are many variations, like the Closed Ruy Lopez, the Marshall Attack, and the Berlin Defense.